    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1078414243" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1078414243" />
    <a title="Anvita" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/35880232-anvita"><img alt="Anvita" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1078414243?book_show_action=true">Oct 12, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anvita" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anvita" href="/user/show/35880232-anvita">Anvita</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1078414243" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13380444831301454209">The book&apos;s protagonist is Aranya, or Arnie and the book talks about her journey as a mother, daughter, niece, sister etc but more importantly an individual. She is faced with an unusual circumstance wherein she has to fight a legal battle against her own family for claiming which is rightfully hers. The book goes back and forth into time to unfold the events which adds to the suspense of the story. As a child, she has faced child abuse by her own mother; as a teenager, she has been endlessly com</span>
  <span id="freeText13380444831301454209" style="display:none">The book's protagonist is Aranya, or Arnie and the book talks about her journey as a mother, daughter, niece, sister etc but more importantly an individual. She is faced with an unusual circumstance wherein she has to fight a legal battle against her own family for claiming which is rightfully hers. The book goes back and forth into time to unfold the events which adds to the suspense of the story. As a child, she has faced child abuse by her own mother; as a teenager, she has been endlessly compared with her brother ; as a wife, she has been subjected to unreasonable accusations of not being a good wife and mother. In spite of all this, she decides to believe in herself and fights for what she believes in. Aranya takes help of Internet and Google to collect important evidence for the case. In fact, the author also comments on the fact that 'Google' has been used as a verb instead of a noun these days which is an interesting observation. <br /><br />The book's protagonist Aranya has a deep impact since even though she has been betrayed by the very people whom she considers her family, she stands up for what she believes in. As individuals, very often we take a lot of relationships like our mother, father, brother, sister or spouse for granted. However, we must have the self-confidence and perseverance to go for whatever we believe in.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13380444831301454209" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

