    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1573525914" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1573525914" />
    <a title="Monika" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2897794-monika"><img alt="Monika" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1403147637p2/2897794.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1573525914?book_show_action=true">Mar 08, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Monika" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Monika" href="/user/show/2897794-monika">Monika</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2897794-monika?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2897794-monika?shelf=fast-paced">fast-paced</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2897794-monika?shelf=indian-authors">indian-authors</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2897794-monika?shelf=2016">2016</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1573525914" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer362766091679717039">Daughter By Court Order is a book on the the life of Aranya, or Arnie, who has been physically and psychologically abused by her own mother all her life and she suddenly discovers that her mother has totally kept her out of the family tree. That she doesn&apos;t exist.<br/><br/>It&apos;s a gripping tale of family fueds and of power play. It is a tale of one woman&apos;s fight to be a recognised as a legal heir and a daughter of the family. It is a powerful book in this time and age when we think we have moved beyond the</span>
  <span id="freeText362766091679717039" style="display:none">Daughter By Court Order is a book on the the life of Aranya, or Arnie, who has been physically and psychologically abused by her own mother all her life and she suddenly discovers that her mother has totally kept her out of the family tree. That she doesn't exist.<br /><br />It's a gripping tale of family fueds and of power play. It is a tale of one woman's fight to be a recognised as a legal heir and a daughter of the family. It is a powerful book in this time and age when we think we have moved beyond the times where we have to fight for the basic rights. The book also beautifully depicts the various facets of relationship of how a girl forms heroes while growing up and how when a grown up woman she deals with all of them deceiving her. <br /><br />What I loved about the book most was the relationship Arnie builds with her own kids inspite of the lack of any link with her own mother or may be she worked extra hard because of that.<br /><br />Also for a change I liked the way the court &amp; lawyers were represented, for some reason they felt real. A mix of honest, corrupt and doing work according to the fee ;)<br /><br />Wonderful &amp; powerful read this one. </span>
  <a data-text-id="362766091679717039" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


