<div id="review_1275517023" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1275517023" />
    <a title="Neerja" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16356602-neerja"><img alt="Neerja" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1275517023?book_show_action=true">May 08, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Neerja" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Neerja" href="/user/show/16356602-neerja">Neerja</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1275517023" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6151084176575855737">Once I started reading Ratna&apos;s &apos;Daughter by Court Order&apos;, I could not put it down!Every time I felt I was not doing justice to savouring it,I&apos;d stop for a while and get back to it. Indeed an excellent read,<br/>the story unfolds seamlessly. Characters etched sharply in the backdrop of a distinct background and since that was my city, I felt a part of it...... red silk cotton trees and all<br/>emails written by the protagonist wrought anguish and whenever one wanted to rubbish the account as contrived or o</span>
  <span id="freeText6151084176575855737" style="display:none">Once I started reading Ratna's 'Daughter by Court Order', I could not put it down!Every time I felt I was not doing justice to savouring it,I'd stop for a while and get back to it. Indeed an excellent read,<br />the story unfolds seamlessly. Characters etched sharply in the backdrop of a distinct background and since that was my city, I felt a part of it...... red silk cotton trees and all<br />emails written by the protagonist wrought anguish and whenever one wanted to rubbish the account as contrived or over dramatised along came a few passages that hit deep.<br />My students wanted to discuss the book and could not fathom how a mother could have been so ....we spent some time unravelling a few relationships...and I saw them grow up just a little then and there.<br />I loved the spontaneity of the dialogue,an extended metaphor of Ratna ....eloquent, expressive ; needless to say it scored brilliantly for being sharp in retort and deliciously vituperative!<br />What a rhetoric against conniving power play!<br />I loved the book and recommend it to all!</span>
  <a data-text-id="6151084176575855737" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


